input.plan:
## Root cause

[`relocation_jobs/static/js/scrape.js`](relocation_jobs/static/js/scrape.js) `fetchOneCompany()` opens a fresh "Fetching…" panel, then calls `syncFetchStateFromServer()` purely to check "is a fetch already running?" before POSTing. But `syncFetchStateFromServer()` is not a passive read — it's the background-polling reconciler:

```js
export async function syncFetchStateFromServer({ toastOnClear = false } = {}) {
  ...
  const clientThinksActive = state.countryFetchActive || state.fetchBusy || state.serverFetchRunning;
  if (st.running) { ... }
  if (clientThinksActive) {
    if (!st.running) {
      applyFetchStatus(st, { replaceLog: true });   // <-- repaints panel with STALE data
    }
    clearFetchActivity({ ... });                    // <-- clears fetchBusy
  }
  return st;
}
```

Since `fetchOneCompany` already set `fetchBusy = true` before this call, `clientThinksActive` is true. The server's `st.running` is `false` (reporting the *previous* completed run), so the reconciler treats it as "the run we were tracking just finished" and repaints the just-opened panel with the old run's `review_jobs`/log via `applyFetchStatus(..., {replaceLog: true})`, then clears `fetchBusy`. Net effect: user sees the old "Fetch complete" + old job list flash for ~1-2s, then the panel flips to real "Fetching… → saving roles…" progress, then genuinely completes. Confirmed via Playwright: reproduced the flash pre-fix, confirmed clean `Starting… → saving roles… → Fetch complete` sequence post-fix, no console/network errors.

## Fix (already drafted, verified, not yet committed)

Use the side-effect-free `getFetchStatus()` (already imported in this file) for the pre-flight check instead of `syncFetchStateFromServer()`:

```js
try {
  const st = await getFetchStatus();
  if (st?.running) {
    toast("A fetch is already running.");
    setFetchBusy(false);
    hideFetchPanelOnFailure();
    return;
  }
} catch {
  // Status check failed — proceed and let fetchCompanyRequest surface the real error.
}
```

This preserves the "block if genuinely running" behavior without triggering the reconciler's stale repaint / `clearFetchActivity` side effects.

## Scope check

`scrape.js` is plain static JS (not part of the Vite/React bundle in `frontend/`), so no `npm run build` is needed — only a panel restart / browser refresh to pick up the change.

## Verification

- Reused ad-hoc Playwright script (Swisslog / Malaysia, admin login) to click "Fetch jobs" and poll the fetch-panel DOM at 2s intervals; confirmed no stale-completion flash, clean state progression, zero console errors.
- No automated test currently covers this frontend flow. Given engineering-standards guidance ("non-trivial logic leaves one runnable check"), propose leaving this as a manual Playwright smoke check documented in the commit message rather than adding a permanent test harness, since there's no existing JS test setup in this repo (no jest/playwright test config found under `relocation_jobs/static` or `frontend/`) — ponytail: no automated coverage for fetch-panel state machine, add if this class of bug recurs or a JS test runner gets introduced.

## Note: unrelated pending diffs in the tree

`git status` shows other uncommitted changes from earlier in this session unrelated to this bug (SAP SuccessFactors ATS fetcher scaffolding in `relocation_jobs/scrape/boards/successfactors.py`, `relocation_jobs/scrape/board.py`, `relocation_jobs/core/ats_constants.py`, plus scaling-proposal docs). This plan only touches `relocation_jobs/static/js/scrape.js`. Not committing anything without explicit confirmation per the `Do not commit unless the user explicitly asks` rule.

